ar production in World War I and World War II (Michael Bliss and Robert Bothwell, respectively), the political implications of organizing American society for war from 1917 to 1945 (Robert Cuff), and the establishment and expansion of wartime British intelligence services in the two World Wars (Christopher Andrew). The essays will be of interest to historians, political scientists, professional soldiers, and readers interested in the story of the two World Wars and the social and cultural aspects of those conflicts.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aIndustrial mobilizationvCongresses. 0aIndustrial mobilizationxCongressesxCanada. 0aIndustrial mobilizationxCongressesxGreat Britain. 0aIndustrial mobilizationxCongressesxUnited States. 0aIndustrial mobilizationzCanadavCongresses. 0aIndustrial mobilizationzGreat BritainvCongresses. 0aIndustrial mobilizationzUnited StatesvCongresses. 0aTotal warxCanadaxGreat BritainxUnited States. 0aTotal war. 0aWar and societyvCongresses. 0aWar and societyxCongresses. 0aWorld War, 1914-1918vCongresses. 0aWorld War, 1914-1918xCongresses. 0aWorld War, 1939-1945vCongresses. 0aWorld War, 1939-1945xCongresses. 4aHistory: Military History. 7aHISTORY / Military / General.2bisacsh1 aAndrew, Christopher M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBliss, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBothwell, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBurk, Kathleen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCuff, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMarwick, Arthur, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eB